goals.question: What is the distribution of population across different age groups and sex?

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['people'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean Age: {data["age"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median Age: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['sex']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    sns.barplot(x='sex', y='counts', data=data, palette='Set2')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of sex in the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Sex')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and population?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'age', 'sex']).sum().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.barplot(x="year", y="people", hue="sex", data=data, palette="muted", ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different age groups and sex?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
